defaults.name: %s_ENVIRONMENT
defaults.description: Changes to the daemon environment.

defaults.name: %s_FLAG
defaults.description: Daemon Flag

defaults.name: SHUTDOWN_FAST_TIMEOUT
defaults.description: Timeout to shutdown fast

defaults.name: PREEN_INTERVAL
defaults.description: Interval at which preen will run

defaults.name: MASTER_NEW_BINARY_DELAY
defaults.description: This macro controls how long it waits before attempting to execute the new binary

defaults.name: MASTER_NEW_BINARY_RESTART
defaults.description: Defines a mode of operation for the restart of the condor_master, when it notices that the condor_master binary has changed

defaults.name: MASTER_CHECK_NEW_EXEC_INTERVAL
defaults.description: This macro controls how often the condor_master checks the timestamps of the running daemons.

defaults.name: %sUPDATE_INTERVAL
defaults.description: This macro determines how often the daemon sends a ClassAd update to the condor_collector

defaults.name: MASTER_RECOVER_FACTOR
defaults.description: A macro to set how long a daemon needs to run without crashing before it is considered recovered.

defaults.name: MASTER_BACKOFF_FACTOR
defaults.description: When a daemon crashes, condor_master uses an exponential back off delay before restarting it.

defaults.name: MASTER_BACKOFF_CEILING
defaults.description: This entry determines the maximum amount of time you want the master to wait between attempts to start a given daemon

defaults.name: MASTER_BACKOFF_CONSTANT
defaults.description: These settings define the constant value of the expression used to determine how long to wait before starting the daemon again (and, effectively becomes the initial backoff time)

defaults.name: SETTABLE_ATTRS_%s
defaults.description: Settings used to restrict the configuration values that can be changed using the condor_config_val command

defaults.name: MASTER_TIMEOUT_MULTIPLIER
defaults.description: This value multiplies configured timeout values for all targeted subsystem communications, thereby increasing the time until a timeout occurs

defaults.name: CCB_ADDRESS
defaults.description: This is the address of a condor_collector that will serve as this daemon's Condor Connection Broker (CCB)

defaults.name: DNS_CACHE_REFRESH
defaults.description: DNS Cache Refresh

defaults.name: MASTER_INSTANCE_LOCK
defaults.description: Defines the name of a file for the condor_master daemon to lock in order to prevent multiple condor_masters from starting.

defaults.name: MASTER_DAEMON_AD_FILE
defaults.description: A complete path to a file that is to contain the ClassAd for a daemon.

defaults.name: COLLECTOR_TCP_SOCKET_BUFSIZE
defaults.description: Collectors internal socket buffer size

defaults.name: SOAP_SSL_PORT
defaults.description: The port number on which SOAP over SSL messages are accepted, when SOAP over SSL is enabled.

defaults.name: QUERY_TIMEOUT
defaults.description: The port number on which SOAP over SSL messages are accepted, when SOAP over SSL is enabled.

defaults.name: VALID_SPOOL_FILES
value: job_queue.log, job_queue.log.tmp, history, Accountant.log, Accountantnew.log, local_univ_execute, .quillwritepassword, .pgpass, .schedd_address, .schedd_classad, OfflineLog
